WEBVTT

00:00.994 --> 00:04.699
Our second scripture reading for the day is indeed the Lord's prayer.

00:04.739 --> 00:10.285
If you want to read along with me, it's on page seven of the New Testament in your pew Bible.

00:10.946 --> 00:14.190
It's Matthew six versus nine through 13.

00:15.131 --> 00:18.035
Will you please stand as we hear the gospel if you're able?

00:29.089 --> 00:30.130
When you pray,

00:30.242 --> 00:30.983
pray this way.

00:32.225 --> 00:35.510
Our Father in heaven, hallowed be your name.

00:36.471 --> 00:37.633
Your kingdom come.

00:38.334 --> 00:41.579
Your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

00:42.561 --> 00:57.203
And give us this day our daily bread and forgive us our debts as we also have forgiven our debtors and do not bring us into the time of trial, but rescue us from the evil one.

00:58.184 --> 00:59.506
This is the word of God.

00:59.906 --> 01:00.928
for the people of God.

01:03.191 --> 01:04.113
You may be seated.

01:08.660 --> 01:13.608
During the last couple of weeks, we've been looking at the Lord's prayer kind of in segments.

01:15.111 --> 01:26.770
And today we're going to take time to look at what I think is probably the least understood and most ignored part of the Lord's prayer that we have.

01:26.914 --> 01:29.938
But I want to start by asking you a question.

01:32.541 --> 01:35.645
Have you ever just wanted to be God for a day?

01:38.929 --> 01:48.460
I mean, be honest that you could control lightning and other elements and just kind of make some commands and rearrange things.

01:49.822 --> 01:56.530
I've had that temptation, you know, but the truth is that's not a new temptation.

01:57.602 --> 02:07.737
Really, all the way back to the beginning with Adam and Eve, the temptation was what the serpent said is, you don't need God.

02:08.678 --> 02:09.419
You got this.

02:14.627 --> 02:15.468
I don't got this.

02:19.695 --> 02:21.938
But we don't learn very quickly.

02:24.930 --> 02:31.096
Generation to generation, people tried to figure out how to make the world work outside of the garden.

02:31.537 --> 02:37.282
And finally, they came to the season where they said, hey, God, we want a king.

02:39.825 --> 02:40.526
We want a king.

02:40.586 --> 02:43.208
And God said, you don't need a king.

02:45.190 --> 02:46.212
Just going to be trouble.

02:47.493 --> 02:48.254
And what do we say?

02:48.274 --> 02:50.676
Nah, we got this.

02:51.497 --> 02:52.658
We just need a king.

02:53.794 --> 02:56.076
So God said, you asked for it.

02:56.957 --> 02:57.438
You got it.

02:58.839 --> 03:00.181
And so who was the first king?

03:02.884 --> 03:03.364
Saul.

03:04.866 --> 03:07.269
Now was Saul a great king?

03:08.310 --> 03:10.672
No, Saul was terrible.

03:11.153 --> 03:19.702
Oh, he was handsome and ready and powerful, but as soon as he was placed in the position of power, he went crazy.

03:21.925 --> 03:23.186
He couldn't handle it.

03:24.642 --> 03:30.708
And so in the midst of the pressure and the power and the temptations, he wrecked Israel.

03:33.491 --> 03:39.958
And so quietly at night in their prayers, the Hebrew people would say, we want another king.

03:43.902 --> 03:45.043
Contestant number two.

03:45.083 --> 03:52.210
And out of the shepherd's field came King David.

03:53.506 --> 04:07.644
the mighty slayer of the giants, the innocent shepherd boy, the one who boldly stood up against the enemies of God's people, and David became king.

04:11.149 --> 04:14.112
And it went okay for a little while.

04:14.132 --> 04:21.682
I mean, Scripture tells us David was a man after God's own heart, but then there were little things like killing

04:22.626 --> 04:26.832
one of your soldiers so that you can commit adultery with his wife.

04:28.415 --> 04:33.642
I mean, little things that just kind of clouded the picture a little bit.

04:36.827 --> 04:39.591
And David tried to repent and he tried to change.

04:42.856 --> 04:52.210
And as he got older and the conflicts grew and the tensions grew and the enemies grew, then there began to be a prayer from

04:52.290 --> 04:53.211
the Hebrew people.

04:56.857 --> 05:02.265
Maybe we need another king.

05:02.285 --> 05:03.447
And then came Solomon.

05:07.373 --> 05:10.017
And his intent was to turn people back to God.

05:10.057 --> 05:11.840
And so he built this beautiful temple.

05:12.321 --> 05:18.791
He created a God centers community, but before he knew it, it had gotten out of his control.

05:19.712 --> 05:21.074
And every since then,

05:21.666 --> 05:24.529
The people have been praying God send us.

05:27.753 --> 05:28.754
Okay, it's been bad.

05:29.014 --> 05:29.995
We'll take David back.

05:31.937 --> 05:32.838
We'll have a do over.

05:32.878 --> 05:47.314
And as the Hebrew people prayed, they prayed that David would come back and be their Messiah and lead them and form and shape a kingdom, bring them back to power, make them, I shouldn't say great again.

05:53.186 --> 05:54.107
but it never happened.

05:58.073 --> 06:02.099
And into that picture comes Jesus.

06:06.605 --> 06:13.595
And as Jesus watches, he sees the fact that's been the pattern of history since the beginning of time.

06:14.176 --> 06:18.162
People want one or two things and

06:18.402 --> 06:20.345
Truly, they want them both at the same time.

06:20.726 --> 06:27.796
We want to be God, but we don't have the capacity to do it, but we want what we want when we want it.

06:30.701 --> 06:47.186
And if we can't be God and be king of our own life, then what we'd really like to have is something kind of like England has, kind of a monarchy that has a king that has all the fruit fruit that goes with it, but we still make all the decisions.

06:48.930 --> 06:57.382
I mean, we like somebody to wear the crown and look royal and we'll go to the palace and pay homage, but we still want to be in control.

06:59.986 --> 07:02.510
Y'all, we're not good at it.

07:04.513 --> 07:06.476
I don't care what political party you're from.

07:06.796 --> 07:08.319
I don't care what country you're from.

07:08.379 --> 07:10.101
I don't care what your heritage is from.

07:10.682 --> 07:16.050
We were not made to rule this world.

07:21.730 --> 07:31.182
And so as Jesus watched his disciples and listened to the buzz of the Hebrew people saying, we want our Messiah to come.

07:31.222 --> 07:33.345
We want David to come and kick the Romans out.

07:33.625 --> 07:39.834
We want to go back to the old ways where we were powerful and in control when they really weren't ever in control.

07:42.317 --> 07:49.426
And so it was not subtle in Jesus' eyes when the disciples asked him to pray

07:51.554 --> 07:55.659
that he worded the prayer the way he did.

07:57.762 --> 07:59.344
I'm going to make another confession.

08:00.045 --> 08:11.879
A lot of times when I'm praying the Lord's prayer and I get to the part where it says, thy kingdom come, thy will be done.

08:11.959 --> 08:17.266
My mouth is saying those words, but my brain is saying my kingdom come.

08:18.754 --> 08:20.216
My will be done.

08:20.577 --> 08:22.039
I just want you to baptize it.

08:23.681 --> 08:24.883
I want you to make it happen.

08:30.070 --> 08:41.406
But what Jesus was truly saying to us and asking us to pray whenever we pray is to say, Dear God, we miss the Garden of Eden.

08:45.532 --> 08:46.994
We miss the way

08:47.106 --> 08:48.748
we were created to live.

08:51.270 --> 08:56.236
We have messed up and we don't have the capacity to change it.

08:58.037 --> 09:02.262
And so here is our prayer.

09:04.204 --> 09:06.767
Thy kingdom come.

09:09.429 --> 09:13.874
Thy will be done on earth.

09:15.906 --> 09:17.008
as it is in heaven.

09:19.731 --> 09:24.157
Jesus reminds us that this place we live is not heaven.

09:25.559 --> 09:26.681
It is not the garden.

09:28.243 --> 09:32.529
It is the place we have perpetually broken.

09:36.094 --> 09:37.235
I don't like hearing that.

09:37.255 --> 09:42.162
I'm an eternal optimist.

09:45.410 --> 09:50.258
But the world we live in is in critical brokenness.

09:52.742 --> 10:02.277
And news alert, no matter who's elected the next president, they will not fix the brokenness.

10:04.901 --> 10:12.914
Whoever's elected your next senator or representative, whoever we politically gather to build a new nation, kingdom,

10:14.402 --> 10:18.768
is not capable of doing that themselves.

10:22.252 --> 10:39.314
And so as Jesus pulled his disciples to him, part of the reason that he asked them to pray that prayer was for them to reframe their thinking where they were no longer thinking, we want King David to come back and go to war and destroy the Romans, he wanted them to think.

10:41.762 --> 10:49.192
I want to love and obey God with everything that I have, regardless of what the world has to say to me.

10:51.655 --> 10:52.777
Thy kingdom come.

10:53.217 --> 10:59.926
Thy will be done is the core of who we should be.

11:00.627 --> 11:11.602
It is simply put a very humbling place that we're called to, a place that puts us

11:12.194 --> 11:34.643
in our souls on our knees in the presence of the most holy Creator that causes us to remind ourselves that we're not nearly as big or powerful or smart as we think we are, not that we're not fearfully and wonderfully made, but we were not made to rule the world.

11:37.447 --> 11:40.050
We were made to follow the one who does.

11:42.306 --> 11:47.233
the one who made it, the one who formed and shaped us.

11:50.517 --> 12:06.258
Our culture is a very dangerous culture to live that out in because we live in a culture that's born around freedom, which was a gift God gave us in the beginning, the freedom of choice, the freedom of deciding how we will live.

12:08.258 --> 12:17.128
But in God's creative purpose, that freedom was always supposed to be couched in loving God first.

12:20.812 --> 12:37.170
In that sixth chapter of Matthew, Jesus teaches us to pray that He is the one that brings provision, that God is the one that brings frame to life, that God has already created the government,

12:39.490 --> 12:40.931
that we were made to live in.

12:40.991 --> 12:49.399
And Jesus put it very simply, love the Lord your God with all your heart, mind, soul and strength and love your neighbor as yourself.

12:49.860 --> 12:55.245
Wouldn't it be cool if that's the only law we needed?

12:57.727 --> 12:59.169
That's the only law they need in heaven.

13:01.051 --> 13:05.475
It's the only way the angels and those who are there in the presence of God live.

13:06.896 --> 13:08.818
It is what we are called

13:08.962 --> 13:09.923
to live into.

13:14.988 --> 13:16.409
I want to ask you another question.

13:20.473 --> 13:30.963
As we read that chapter in Luke, one of the things that Jesus said to kind of flesh out this kingdom of God was, what does it look like to live in the kingdom of God?

13:31.544 --> 13:37.970
And Jesus uses this beautiful litany of natural things, the lilies,

13:38.242 --> 13:39.143
The birds.

13:41.346 --> 13:51.922
You know, so many times in our mind, we think if we don't take control and do these things and don't misunderstand me, I don't think that we can walk through life thinking God makes every decision.

13:53.083 --> 14:01.756
But what I do believe is we can walk through life believing that God is indeed looking out for our best interest and for our provision.

14:02.637 --> 14:06.002
Maybe not at the level we expect.

14:09.826 --> 14:15.812
And so Jesus said to him, take no care for what you will eat or for what you will wear.

14:16.272 --> 14:22.859
Do you ever think about the story of creation and think about, what was the first realization that Adam and Eve made?

14:25.761 --> 14:26.482
We're naked.

14:34.290 --> 14:38.834
Maybe if we hadn't sinned, we'd all be in the biggest, nudist colony in the world.

14:40.834 --> 14:44.080
You wouldn't have to go buy clothes or figure out what matched or what didn't.

14:44.180 --> 14:46.585
And you wouldn't be caught up in the middle of that.

14:49.010 --> 14:50.152
You know what I found in my life?

14:50.633 --> 15:03.538
Most of the wounds and the tribulation I face are self-inflicted because I've tried to make decisions I really didn't have to make.

15:09.602 --> 15:24.339
What I've found with most people who are coming to the faith is, they may know the Lord's prayer, but they don't really believe in prayer.

15:28.543 --> 15:29.084
Do you hear me?

15:32.688 --> 15:34.290
We can say those words.

15:37.346 --> 15:39.648
But the truth is prayer is more than words.

15:41.550 --> 15:45.214
Let's back up to that phrase that we're focusing on today.

15:45.734 --> 15:52.301
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done.

15:53.782 --> 15:54.923
You know what that infers?

15:59.708 --> 16:02.251
We don't get that by talking.

16:04.413 --> 16:05.714
We get that by listening.

16:09.858 --> 16:13.424
Prayer's not prayer if we're not listening.

16:15.587 --> 16:20.756
Prayer's not a dialogue if God is not speaking to us and giving us direction.

16:22.378 --> 16:24.301
And we can get caught up in all the technicalities.

16:24.321 --> 16:26.144
Well, how do I know if it's God?

16:26.805 --> 16:29.169
Does he sound like Morgan Freeman?

16:29.570 --> 16:32.615
Or what does God sound like?

16:35.499 --> 16:37.202
Well, the truth be told,

16:37.314 --> 16:40.740
It's been my experience that when God speaks to us, our soul knows.

16:41.802 --> 16:44.026
That may sound like a cheap way out, but it's not.

16:46.230 --> 16:51.499
But here's the last conversation I want us to have along with this that I need to make you aware of.

16:52.661 --> 16:57.650
You see, the importance of what Jesus was teaching

16:57.730 --> 17:03.176
them as they prayed to say, thy kingdom come, thy will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

17:03.497 --> 17:06.120
There's another phrase deeper down into the prayer.

17:06.160 --> 17:11.726
We'll look at more depth that lead us not into what?

17:11.746 --> 17:12.487
Temptation.

17:13.028 --> 17:14.349
You want to know why that's in there?

17:14.650 --> 17:19.856
Is because when we seek God's will, it's exactly like in the beginning temptation.

17:20.416 --> 17:25.362
Every time we have a choice to make, guess who shows up to give us another choice.

17:30.274 --> 17:33.399
That's another reason God gave us the gift of decision.

17:34.361 --> 17:36.665
We have to choose what voice we listen to.

17:38.568 --> 17:47.022
When Sidney and I were in seminary, our first job, we had gone, we were promised a job, we went to get there, we got to the school and they said, oh, we forgot you.

17:48.565 --> 17:49.426
It was delightful.

17:49.954 --> 17:55.842
We had no place to live, so we found this little apartment that was about the size of an inside of a refrigerator.

17:55.882 --> 18:00.628
You could literally step out of the bed into the commode, you know, if you weren't careful.

18:01.149 --> 18:02.892
It was just a tiny thing.

18:03.212 --> 18:10.962
The kitchen was decorated with Christmas paper that some guys had lived in before had literally stuck on the walls and we had to peel it off.

18:10.983 --> 18:17.211
There was so much mildew on the big window that you had to take a scraper to scrape it off.

18:17.251 --> 18:19.474
Other than that, it was good.

18:20.514 --> 18:32.627
We took the last money we had, we paid for that, and then I went looking for a job a few days, and finally it was one of those days, and those of you couples know these days, I came home and Cindy looked at me and said, don't come home tomorrow without a job.

18:35.471 --> 18:36.311
I came home with two.

18:39.475 --> 18:42.158
The main job was a place where we got a new place to live.

18:42.719 --> 18:49.426
We got the job, I got the job as a night manager in a 15-story senior adult retirement center.

18:51.330 --> 19:01.784
All I had to do was answer all the emergency calls during the night, let the paper man in at five o'clock in the morning and help around inspecting as we locked up at night.

19:04.267 --> 19:05.508
Y'all old people are wild.

19:08.833 --> 19:14.780
I could tell you stories for years, but it didn't take us long to decide that wasn't where God had called us to work.

19:15.161 --> 19:16.082
That was just so

19:16.354 --> 19:20.440
Literally one night we just got on our knees and said, Lord, you got to help us.

19:20.540 --> 19:28.191
You got to help us find a place to be that we really need to be before we die or something happens.

19:30.053 --> 19:33.338
Literally the next day I got three phone calls.

19:37.744 --> 19:40.768
The first one was my dream phone call.

19:41.690 --> 19:44.914
I love to preach more and I love to eat.

19:45.026 --> 19:47.448
I was going to seminary mostly because I had to.

19:49.170 --> 19:54.956
And one of the district superintendents called because in his words, he knew those Mississippi boys could preach.

19:57.038 --> 20:03.163
And he offered me a full time church that was incredible.

20:05.305 --> 20:09.329
And as soon as he hung up, I want to say yes, but then another call came.

20:11.211 --> 20:14.194
And then another call that was in a little church

20:14.690 --> 20:24.980
Not that little out in Marietta that not only had a youth associate position, but it had a position for an administrative assistant or a secretary.

20:27.363 --> 20:30.226
Then as we prayed about it, we really knew that was meeting.

20:30.806 --> 20:32.528
It meant every need we had.

20:33.629 --> 20:42.258
And what I began to realize in retrospect was that other offer was my temptation.

20:48.066 --> 20:49.908
not God's provision.

20:53.572 --> 20:59.939
And the miraculous thing that happened was, as we both fell in love with that church, they loved and cared and watched over us.

21:00.320 --> 21:07.508
I had a mentor who was an incredible administrator and teacher, and I probably learned more from him than I ever learned in seminary.

21:13.815 --> 21:16.978
Thy will be done.

21:19.426 --> 21:24.613
Praying that prayer is not easy because it requires us to listen.

21:26.296 --> 21:28.499
It requires us to humble ourselves.

21:29.741 --> 21:36.470
It requires us to turn out the noise of the world and to focus on the way of God.

21:38.012 --> 21:44.461
Today we celebrate the sacrament of communion and it's this incredible gift that we miss all the layers of.

21:44.982 --> 21:47.826
One of the layers is this

21:48.930 --> 21:50.192
is the king's table.

21:54.277 --> 22:02.608
This is the place we come to break bread with our Lord, where God Himself and Jesus Christ meets us at the table.

22:02.869 --> 22:13.603
And in the presence of His Holy Spirit seeks to infiltrate our souls and impress upon us the ways of His kingdom so that we can walk out those doors.

22:14.164 --> 22:15.986
And as the litany says,

22:16.066 --> 22:25.317
as these elements become the body of Christ for us in the Holy Spirit, we become the body of Christ for the world.

22:26.639 --> 22:42.578
And we march out this door as ambassadors for the King, not as Republicans or Democrats, even though we are, whether we like it or not, but first and foremost, as servants.

22:45.141 --> 22:46.002
Servants.

22:47.266 --> 22:48.587
of the God of creation.

22:50.970 --> 22:57.958
So today as you kneel, it's not just part of the litany.

23:00.121 --> 23:11.914
As we ask you to kneel, it is a symbol of humility and submission and honor.

23:14.096 --> 23:15.538
And for those of you

23:16.130 --> 23:18.033
who can't physically kneel.

23:18.513 --> 23:36.978
It is that time in your heart to be brought low in the presence of the Almighty Creator and to remind yourself that the God we worship here knows what He's doing.

23:39.778 --> 23:58.136
that the God we worship here is more powerful than any earthly power and that the God we worship here will be here long after we're gone and hopefully when we're in the kingdom with Him.

24:00.798 --> 24:06.844
This prayer calls us not to be of this world, but to be of the Creator.

24:08.485 --> 24:09.106
Let us pray.

